{"cwd": "/tmp/cch-sandboxes/20260613T063051/websearch-tool", "duration_ms": 7248, "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "session_id": "<SESSION_ID>", "tool_input": {"query": "claude code hooks"}, "tool_name": "WebSearch", "tool_response": {"durationSeconds": 7.247905217, "query": "claude code hooks", "results": [{"content": [{"title": "GitHub - karanb192/claude-code-hooks: 🪝 A growing collection of useful Claude Code hooks. Copy, paste, customize.", "url": "https://github.com/karanb192/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "GitHub - disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery: Master Claude Code Hooks · GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: A Practical Guide to Workflow Automation | DataCamp", "url": "https://www.datacamp.com/tutorial/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Automate Your AI Coding Workflow", "url": "https://www.ksred.com/claude-code-hooks-a-complete-guide-to-automating-your-ai-coding-workflow/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks Complete Guide — Automate and Enforce Rules Reliably - SmartScope", "url": "https://smartscope.blog/en/generative-ai/claude/claude-code-hooks-guide/"}, {"title": "Claude Code & Agent SDK Hooks (2026): PreToolUse, PostToolUse, UserPromptSubmit, Stop, SubagentStop Reference", "url": "https://www.morphllm.com/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Why Each of My 95 Hooks Exists", "url": "https://blakecrosley.com/blog/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code hooks 是用户定义的 shell 命令,在 Claude Code 生命周期的各个点执行。Hooks 提供对 Claude Code 行为的确定性控制,确保某些操作总是发生,而不是依赖 LLM 选择运行它们。", "url": "https://docs.anthropic.com/zh-CN/docs/claude-code/hooks-guide"}], "tool_use_id": "srvtoolu_01MXzVL9N3wc8dZXedumQTsX"}, "Based on the search results, here's what Claude Code hooks are:\n\n## Overview\n\nClaude Code hooks are shell scripts that execute at specific lifecycle points during Claude Code sessions, firing deterministically at specific moments like before a tool runs (PreToolUse), after it completes (PostToolUse), when you send a prompt.\n\n## Key Benefits\n\nHooks work like git hooks, but for your AI agent, allowing you to define handlers—shell commands, LLM prompts, or even sub-agents—that fire automatically at specific points during Claude Code's execution. Hooks inject deterministic processing into Claude Code's lifecycle, and unlike prompt instructions which Claude may interpret flexibly, hooks execute the same way every time.\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\nClaude Code Hooks let you automate reminders by running shell commands automatically at specific points in your workflow, such as setting up hooks for code formatting, test execution, notifications, and file protection.\n\n## How They Work\n\nIn Claude Code a hook is a shell command that reads JSON from stdin and signals back through exit codes and stdout JSON. As of March 2026, Claude Code Hooks has grown into a full-fledged automation platform with 21 lifecycle events, 4 handler types, async execution, and JSON structured output."], "searchCount": 1}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01HyCs8WtE1XCGqzY5SmCot7", "transcript_path": "<TRANSCRIPT_PATH>"}
